---- MODULE MCDieHarder -----
-------------------------MODULE FillJug-------------------------------------
(**************************************************************************)
(* The following definitions duplicate the original die hard example.           *)
                                                                            (* We use this module, which extends DieHarder to define a function MCCapacity and have TLC              *) 
                                                    (* substitute it for Capacity.) Since we need to know values of Jug (which is a             *)  
(* function having Domain as its domain), so also defined MCCapacity.     *)(* And told that in the configuration file, substituted MCCapacity with    */ 
                                                    (* capacity instead) and asked for jug value which will be used to define Capacity.)      )(*)  
                                                                            *)
CONSTANTS Goal = <4> Jug  <- MCCapacity     ****/ This is the definition of capacities. It's a function that takes in capacity as its domain and returns jug value  */    (* The goal for filling up jugs, which can be any integer from above *)
VARIABLES Capacity   /\* set to hold JugCapacity **/     /* This is the variable holding capacities of different types. It's a function that takes in capacity as its domain and returns jug value */ 
                                                                            (* The goal for filling up jugs, which can be any integer from above *)                                                    )(*)  
